GEORGE W. WHITE, Respondent, v. CHARLES WHITE, et al., Appellants.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and Freedman, ,J.

Decided June 6, 1881. Appeal from order denying defendants’ motion to make certain parts of the complaint more definite and certain, or to strike them out as irrelevant and redundant. F. O. Bowman, for appellants. , George H. Adams, for respondent. Per Curiam.

The order should be affirmed, witit costs.
